1. Clone the git repository from https://github.com/vijimscse/PhotoEditor.git in Android Studio
2. Run the project once the IDE gradle setup is done
3. Connect the device to system using USB cable
4. PhotoEditor gets displayed on the device connected.
5. Using Photo Editor, Now you can edit your photo in multiple ways
    * Choose image From gallery
    * You can use camera
    * Image splashing techniques
    * Rotate your image clockwise/ counter clockwise
    * Save image to collections
    * Edit the saved file from collection list
    